Okay everyone. I have a shop I need to build up some small parts inventory at and am looking for the best small parts organizer bins/boxes/containers/whatever your vendor of choice calls them. Currently in the lead is the HDX15 because you can get 2 for $12 at Home Depot, but I don’t love these as there isn’t much space for a good label on the front, and I’m not a huge fan of the dividers.

This is mostly for small parts stuff like screws, nuts, washers, bearings, etc.

It seems a lot of the options that have been popular in the past have been discontinued or disappeared, and I am struggling to find good options. There used to be a few AmazonBasics ones that were very good but I can no longer find those. I’m hoping to figure this out by Friday/Monday, so any and all suggestions are welcome!

(I put the year in the thread title because these products seem to come and go quite a bit).
